value.value: A SI unit of area measurement equal to a square whose sides are one meter long. Square meter is equal to 10,000 square centimeters; 0.01 are; 1.196 square yards; 10.76 square feet; 1550 square inches.
A morphologic variant of leiomyoma characterized by the presence of pleomorphic muscle cells with bizarre hyperchromatic nuclei and eosinophilic cytoplasm.

A SI unit of volume or capacity equal to the volume of a cube with edges one meter in length. It is equal to 1,000 liters; 1,000 cubic decimeters; 10(e+6) cubic centimeters; 25.3 cubic feet; 6.29 barrels.
A SI derived unit of both speed (scalar) and velocity (vector), defined as the distance of one meter travelled per unit time equal to one second.
Meter per second squared is a SI unit of acceleration.
The SI unit of wave number, the spatial analogue of frequency; closely related to the concept of the wave vector.
An indication of the type of unit of measure being used to express a time.
An indication of the type of unit of measure being used to express a mass density.

A SI derived unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one kilogram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic meter, or the concentration of one milligram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one milliliter, or one gram of a substance per one liter of the mixture. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one milliliter.

A SI derived unit of specific volume, a property of materials defined as the number of cubic meters occupied by one kilogram of a particular substance. Specific volume is inversely proportional to density.
An indication of the type of unit of measure being used to express a length or distance.
An indication of the type of unit of measure being used to express a mass.

An aggressive malignant mesenchymal neoplasm with skeletal muscle differentiation, occurring in adults and rarely in children.  The tumor is characterized by the presence of bizarre round, spindle, and polygonal cells.  Clinical presentation includes a rapidly enlarging painful mass usually of the lower extremities.

An approved exemption to the requirement for a participant to meet eligibility criteria prior to study enrollment.  A sponsor-approved waiver is necessary when a subject fails to meet enrollment criteria, but wishes to be accrued to the trial.
A shortened version of a speech or written text, containing only the main points.

PP2A core enzyme consists of a 36-kDa catalytic C subunit and a constant 65-kDa regulatory/structural A subunit that interact with either a B regulatory subunit or with cell signaling molecules, that likely modulate substrate selectivity, catalytic activity, and subcellular localization, yielding the trimeric holoenzyme. Combinations of different subunit isoforms can generate many forms of PP2A, which may differ in substrate specificity, subcellular localization, or tissue specific expression.
A hamartoma that is characterized by the presence of chondroid elements.

label.value: Rhabdomyosarcoma with Mixed Embryonal and Alveolar Features

value.value: A rhabdomyosarcoma composed of embryonic and alveolar components. It is characterized by the presence of spindle cells with myoblastic differentiation, a myxoid stroma, and fibrous septa.  These tumors were previously considered variants of alveolar rhabdomyosarcoma.  The lack of PAX3-FOXO1 fusions in most of these tumors suggests that are biologically and clinically related to embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma.
This gene is involved in signal transduction and the regulation of both cell mobility and morphology.
A chromosome band present on 11q
Serine/threonine-protein kinase PAK 1 (545 aa, ~61 kDa) is encoded by the human PAK1 gene. This protein is involved in both protein phosphorylation and signal transduction.
A retinoblastoma that occurs in a patient without a family history of the disease.

A normal feature of responses to infectious agents that allows recognition of multiple antigenic targets, Epitope Spreading involves non-cross-reactive epitopes, distinct from the inducing epitope, becoming major targets of an ongoing immune response. Epitope spreading (ES) involves an increased presentation of cryptic epitopes on one protein (intermolecular ES) or dominant epitopes on neighboring molecules (intramolecular ES). The result is an increase in antibody repertoire diversify, resulting in an enhanced overall immune response. Conversely, epitope spreading is the primary immunopathogenic event in autoimmune diseases.
A well differentiated mucinous neoplasm that arises from the appendix.  It is characterized by slow growth and it is associated with the development of pseudomyxoma peritonei.
The common saw-tooth architectural pattern observed within hyperplastic polyps.

The salt form of diazo compounds, compounds containing the N2 nitrogen attached to only one hydrocarbon, formulated by replacing three hydrogen atoms of the salt of an aryl primary amine by nitrogen having the general structure represented as R-N2X.

A rare benign mesenchymal neoplasm arising from skeletal muscle. It is characterized by the presence of immature spindle and polygonal cells within a scant myxoid stroma. It usually develops in the head and neck region of young children.
The area above or over the sella turcica.
A basic or essential attribute shared by all members of a class.
The finding of bodily harm due to the poisonous effects associated with the action or administration of therapeutic agents.
A program that gives a computer instructions that provide the user with tools to accomplish a task.
Someone from whom you are descended (but usually more remote than a grandparent).
A benign mesenchymal neoplasm arising from skeletal muscle and occurring in adults.
A shortened form of a word or phrase.
An indication of whether the item in question is an active item.
A registry item for which administrative information is recorded in an Administration Record.
The words or language units by which a thing is known.
Indicates the person or authoritative body who has given approval.
It is the attribute of the object which is to be protected. It along with the object id forms the unique key which can identify the protection element.
This name represents the name that should be used to get all the configuration for authentication for this application.
This gene is involved in carbohydrate metabolism, signal transduction and the regulation of apoptosis.
